Paper: hep-th/9703092

Date: 1997-03-12

Title: Consistent and covriant anomalies in the overlap formulation of chiral

gauge theoriesAuthors: S. Randjbar-Daemi, J. Strathdee

Comments: 10 pages, Latex

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B402 (1997) 134-140

In this letter we show how the covariant anomaly emerges in the overlapscheme. We also prove that the overlap scheme correctly reproduces the anomalyin the flavour currents such as $j^5_\mu$ in vector like theories like QCD.